President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in American Samoa due to high surf, high winds, and flooding from July 12 to July 15, 2022. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The territory and certain private nonprofit organizations can receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures will also receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis. Benigno B. Ruiz has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.